rComments: At first he seems standoffish but that's just his demeanor. A very caring Professor, extremely intelligent, and goes out of his way to make sure his student succeed. No surprises on his tests or exams so if you fail it's your own fault.

I only took his class for the credit, but it turned out to be my favourite class this semester. He is a wonderful professor and very easy to talk to - even if your Italian isn't the greatest. He explains the material very well and if you don't understand it is willing to go through it until you do. He clearly wants his students to succeed.
